00:02:12.330 --> 00:02:27.419
What Football Player Could Be Doing Wrong:
If the ball is popping straight up or going

00:02:27.419 --> 00:02:31.249
in the opposite direction of where you want
it to go on the pop you are hitting the wrong

00:02:31.249 --> 00:02:33.339
part of your foot.

00:02:33.339 --> 00:02:39.529
If you hit closer to your heel that’s like
the ball hitting a wall.

00:02:39.529 --> 00:02:43.819
You want to hit the ball near the base of
your toes so that part of your foot acts like

00:02:43.819 --> 00:02:47.539
a ramp and causes the ball to pop up and go
over your foot.

00:02:47.539 --> 00:02:49.199
Bonus Tips!

00:02:49.199 --> 00:02:54.709
Mastering this trick is easier in tennis shoes
on concrete because you get a better bounce

00:02:54.709 --> 00:02:55.800
off your foot.

00:02:55.800 --> 00:03:00.770
If you do this move in the grass make sure
you are not in thick grass because if you

00:03:00.770 --> 00:03:05.429
are your foot will be buried in the grass
and you won’t get that ball ramping action

00:03:05.429 --> 00:03:06.429
going!

00:03:06.429 --> 00:03:09.569
This trick is very difficult so don’t get
discouraged.

00:03:09.569 --> 00:03:12.020
Keep practicing and have fun trying it!

